task.summary: Created LibraryDomain package and moved over applicable files, and set project to the necessary version of java for andriod development. Note that the code in its current state is not runnable.

Changed load methods to accept either an input stream or use previous functionality. Got rid of checkedOut field on Inventory item in favor of the method returning based on presence of a due date. Changed java compatibility back to version 8 to get rid of squiggly lines and test new code.
Still need to alter code to play nice with android's version of java. Code is runnable when set to java 8 compatibility.
Converted to be compatible with java 6. Got rid of opportunity for stale data in inventory item class.
Converted to be compatible with java 6. Got rid of opportunity for stale data in inventory item class.
Implemented comparable on InventoryItem and altered Library's sort function to take advantage of this.
Got a start on new UI. Will continue to work on this tomorrow.

Login and setup working, moving on to table view tomorrow. Also moved data files into new Data folder in top level directory for easier referencing and got FileProcessor working properly with the new member and staff classes.

Finalized new UI and updates to various domain classes to bring them more in line with what is going in with the android application. Comments pretty much done, just need to clean up unused code and classes.
